    "For the symplectic bosons, we defineξ -= -e -ϕ 1 -iκ 1, η + = e ϕ 1 ∂(e iκ 1), ξ + = e ϕ 2 +iκ 2, η -= e -ϕ 2 ∂(e -iκ 2),(2.19)whereϕ i (z)ϕ j (w) ∼ -δ ij log(z -w), κ i (z)κ j (w) ∼ -δ ij log(z -w).Similarly, for the complex fermions,χ + = e iq 1, ψ -= -e -iq 1, ψ + = e iq 2, χ -= e -iq 2,where q i (z)q j (w) ∼ -δ ij log(z -w).We have in some sense extended our theory through this bosonization by introducing the fields ζ + = e ϕ 1 +iκ 1 and ζ -= e -ϕ 2 -iκ 2.",
    "However, as is noted in [15], these fields can be seen as a formal trick that do not add additional physical states to the theory.",
    "The embedding maps from the worldsheet to CP 1 × CP 1, where we think of (ξ +, ξ -) and (η +, η -) as projective coordinates on each CP 1.",
